file=Cybersecurity/keyring/operational/agent/keyring-config.md · tb=\| Field \| Referenced by \| Value \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| identity_provider (IdP/SSO) \| identity-lifecycle / access-reviews \| `<FILL_IN — the IdP; executes grants/revokes>` \| · tb=\| role_access_baselines_path \| identity-lifecycle / access-reviews / access_review.py \| `<FILL_IN — role → least-privilege entitlement sets>` \| · tb=\| access_review_cadence \| access-reviews \| `<FILL_IN — suggested quarterly, mirrors Fleet Charter Rail 2>` \| · tb=\| privileged_review_cadence \| privileged-access-management \| `<FILL_IN — shorter than normal>` \| · tb=\| pam_tool \| privileged-access-management \| `<FILL_IN — just-in-time / break-glass executor>` \| · tb=\| secrets_manager \| secrets-governance \| `<FILL_IN — the vault; holds + rotates>` \| · tb=\| secret_rotation_cadence \| secrets-governance \| `<FILL_IN>` \| · tb=\| deprovision_sla \| identity-lifecycle \| `<FILL_IN — leaver time-to-deprovision target>` \| · tb=\| executor \| all (the inversion) \| operator / IdP / PAM / vault (keyring holds no keys) \| · tb=\| hr_signal_source \| identity-lifecycle \| `<FILL_IN — future People & Culture / HR joiner-leaver feed>` \| · i:=1. No IdP → manual access matrix, reconciled on cadence (identity-lifecycle fallback), labeled manual.\n2. No `role_access_baselines_path` → access-reviews builds provisional baselines from current-minus-excess; sharpens over cycles.\n3. No `secrets_manager` → top register risk (plaintext secrets); interim encrypted store, labeled provisional.\n4. `executor` is fixed to operator/IdP/PAM/vault — no config grants keyring key-holding or execution (the security-inversion).\n · f:=Unfilled config degrades loudly. The absolute: keyring never holds keys or executes a grant/revoke/rotation — the operator/IdP/PAM/vault does.\n